DESCRIPTION:Join us on Saturday\, May 9\, from 1 - 3 PM at Whispering Vine Fourth St. for a tasting featuring 30+ Pinot Noir alongside passed flatbread from the Fourth St. kitchen.\nTasting Fee: $55 per person\nReserve your spot on Tock: https://www.exploretock.com/whisperingvine4thstreet\nFeatured Wines:\n- Kosta Browne Barrel Auction Pinot Noir 2021 – Winery $165 – This limited Sonoma County Barrel Auction release is built from Gap’s Crown\, Keefer Ranch\, Bootlegger’s Hill and Treehouse Vineyard fruit.\n- Rochioli Estate Pinot Noir 2021 – $99.99 – 94 Robert Parker's Wine Advocate.\n- Paul Hobbs Russian River Pinot Noir 2023 – Winery $80 – 95 James Suckling.\n- Martinelli "Bondi Home Ranch" Russian River Valley Pinot Noir 2022 – Winery $85 – 96 Jeb Dunnuck.\n- Louis Jadot Beaune Clos des Couchereaux Premier Cru 2023 – Winery $80 – 93 Wine Spectator.\nCome explore 30+ Pinot Noir Wines and find your favorite bottle. Discover your favorite pour from the lineup.
LOCATION:4201 W Fourth St Reno\, NV 89523
SUMMARY:Passion for Pinot Party
